TUNIS, March 21 (Xinhua) -- Tunisia on Monday expressed its strong condemnation of attacks targeting sites in Saudi Arabia. "Tunisia firmly condemned the attacks that targeted vital sites as well as economic establishments in Saudi Arabia," according to a statement released by the Tunisian Foreign Ministry. "Tunisia expresses its total solidarity with the Saudi people and reaffirms its support for the kingdom," read the statement. Yemen's Houthi militia on Sunday claimed responsibility for an attack against a Saudi Aramco oil facility in the Saudi Red Sea port city of Jeddah and other vital energy facilities in the Saudi southwestern city of Jazan, the second of such cross-border missile attacks against Saudi Arabia in less than 24 hours.  â– 